@page "/security"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Security - grow.IT</PageTitle>

<div class="contact-page footer-info-page">
    <section class="contact-hero">
        <span class="contact-kicker">Security</span>
        <h1>Security matters because organizations are trusting Grow.IT with real operating data.</h1>
        <p>Grow.IT is built with authenticated access, tenant-aware data boundaries, role-based permissions, audit trails, and controlled email/reporting workflows.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-grid-section">
        <div class="contact-grid">
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Role-based access</h2>
                <p>Users are assigned roles so team members only access the areas and actions appropriate for their work.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Organization separation</h2>
                <p>Tenant-scoped data boundaries keep each organization's records separate inside the platform.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Audit visibility</h2>
                <p>Administrative changes, access attempts, invite activity, report activity, and other sensitive actions are tracked for review.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-form-section">
        <article class="contact-form-card">
            <h2>Responsible disclosure</h2>
            <p>If you believe you found a vulnerability, contact us with the affected area, steps to reproduce, expected impact, and your contact information. Please do not access, copy, or modify data that does not belong to you.</p>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-cta">
        <div class="contact-cta-card">
            <h2>Need security details for review?</h2>
            <p>We can provide additional context for procurement, board, or implementation conversations.</p>
            <div class="contact-cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact?subject=Security%20Question" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Security Team</a>
                <a href="/privacy" class="btn btn-outline">Read Privacy Policy</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
